Fact, Query, Rule, Scheme
public class Predicate
extends java.util.ArrayList<Parameter>
implements java.lang.Comparable<Predicate>

A Predicate is the super class for the four Datalog types- Fact, Scheme, Rule, and Query. A predicate consists of a name and a list of Parameters.

compareTo

public int compareTo(Predicate o)
Compares this Predicate to another Predicate. A Predicate is greater than another Predicate if: - the value of one is greater than another according to String's compareTo method - a Parameter of one is greater than its counterpart using Parameter's compareTo method - a Predicate has more parameters the other

Specified by:
compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Predicate>
Parameters:
o - the Predicate to compare this Predicate to
Returns:
1 if this is greater, -1 if it is less than, or 0 if they are equal
